e that allows users with no

EAT-based Genetic
> Art applet that is integrated into a massive growing "t=
ree of life"

publish
> it to the world and thereby permanently add their creations to th=
e
> ever-expanding tree of life.

> What makes Picbreeder particularly po=
werful and unique is that you
> can *branch* from the published work of any=
 other user that has come
> before.  In other words, you do not have to beg=
in from scratch.
> Instead, for example, if you want to a evolve a face, yo=
u can branch
> from one of the many published faces and explore an infinite=
 number
> of variations from that starting point.
> 
> Perhaps most intrigu=
ing is that we do not know what is possible to
> evolve.  As lineages are b=
uilt upon lineages, complexification in
> NEAT means that images can theore=
tically become more and more
> complex.  Thus, in theory, anything is possi=
ble.  In this sense
> Picbreeder's users are pioneers, exploring collective=
ly a space that
> has never been exhaustively explored and discovering toge=
ther
> creations that no one of us could have discovered alone.
